HEADWORD: Piliferous
<hw>Pi*lif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pilus</ets> hair + <ets>-ferous</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pilif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bearing a single
slender bristle, or hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Beset with hairs.</def>⟦br⟧
